message.content: cs.SD, cs.SD is the most likely sub-category as the paper deals with audio classification and sound event detection tasks. Other likely sub-categories could be cs.CV (computer vision) as the authors used CNNs originating from AlexNet and VGG, cs.LG (machine learning) as CNNs are a popular machine learning technique, cs.SI (sound and music computing) as the paper deals with audio data, and cs.CL (computation and language) as the paper involves natural language processing tasks such as acoustic scene classification.
